Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Jalama
Description: A beach park with several different surf spots. The area has multiple beach breaks and a fast reef break. The spots can hold fairly large waves, commonly seeing overhead surf in the winter time. The beach park includes a campsite, making it a fun place for a little overnight surf trip.

Name: Rincon
Description: A point break wave that offers extremely long rides. Waves can range greatly in size, but almost always attract a large crowd. Very fun surf if you're willing to deal with a pack of people!

Name: Maliubu
Description: A point break with very long rides. Wave height can vary greatly with the swell, but most often Malibu offers very picteresque longboard waves that roll on forever. On larger swells, size can increase greatly and offer long breaking overhead waves.

Name: The Wedge
Description: A shorebreak/beachbreak that is built to destroy. Waves compile their energy along a jetty and form a large,  peaking wave that caves right next to shore. The Wedge offers giant barrels, giant airs, and giant wipeouts.

Name: Black's Beach
Description: A fast and hollow wave that somewhat resembles waves on the North Shore of Oahu. Black's Beach offers some of California's best barells. It breaks best in the Winter time as it recieves a lot more NW swell, which bring in the waves it's famous for.
